### 2. **`.gitignore`**:
The `.gitignore` file helps you avoid committing unnecessary or sensitive files to the repository.

#### Example:
```gitignore
# System files
.DS_Store

# Editor files
.idea/
.vscode/

# Logs and temporary files
*.log
*.tmp

# Python cache files
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]

# Compiled binaries
*.o
*.out
*.exe

# Docker image cache
**/.dockerignore

# Build artifacts
*.dSYM
*.class
*.jar
*.tar
*.gz
*.zip

# Node.js modules
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*

# Secrets and environment files
*.env
*.secret
